phrases: What are you just standin' there for?
Ri'ko, how about openin' the door?!
Do you come here often, too?
This is Brother Jun's family's shop.
If you would like, why do not you come over to my place to watch them practice?
How we going to have a session?
Ri-chan, did not your dad tell you that outsiders are not allowed down here?
Yurika-san is our friend, so I am sure Dad would not mind.
I am just going to get a little fresh air.
All my friends are off at cram school...
Then how about we play together?
That thing's a relic, so sometimes it gets ornery.
At a time like this, you have to work a little magic on it.
How did that get it to work?
Hello, is this the Children's Telephone Counseling Office?
See, there is this boy, Hashiguchi-kun, who is always mean to me.
He hides my slippers, pulls my hair...
What do you think I should do?
You know, maybe that Hashiguchi-kun actually likes you, Sachiko-chan.
My guess is he wants to be friends with you,
but does not know how to express his feelings,
so he acts out like that without really thinking about it.
Recently, I made the girl that I really like cry, too.
I want to apologize to her...
I cannot stay mad at you...
There is something I have to tell you...
Coincidentally, I have been going to the shop for a while.
I had no idea it was your family's...
Actually, there is someone that I like...
Right now... he is the only one I can think of...
I am flattered by the way you feel about me, Kaoru-san...
Here, eat this an' cheer up.
I said something terrible to Kaoru-san...
Kaoru-san might not come back here again...
It is impossible to talk about romantic stuff here in this house...
Why did not you come over for practice during winter vacation?
The teacher told me to give this to you...
that I cannot bring myself to talk about anything.
What are you doing out there?!
Ri'ko is lonely without you around.
Come on, all you got to do is stop by the shop...
I am not going back there again.
I thought I heard a loud noise coming from here a minute ago.
Actually, I wanted to give you this letter.
It is from Shizu-san, our old housekeeper, remember?
We have had our problems over the years...
She got your mother's address and insisted I pass it on to you.
We split up when you were still little,
so you might not remember your mom very well...
But if you would like to go see her, you could, maybe on your next break...
I know this is sudden and may leave you at a loss,
but whether you go or not is totally up to you.
Well, I will let you get back to your studies.
You can bring her some sweet rice treats as a souvenir.
I never said I was going.
Right now, I am just not up to it...
You know where she is now, and if you lose this chance
you will regret it for the rest of your life!
Kaoru-kun, you are hiding something, are not you?
Blue trains basically refers to limited express trains from Asakaze on
that have dedicated blue sleeper cars.
Did you know that the design of the front and back car are different
because they have to switch off being the lead car?
Come to think of it, this is my first time traveling alone.
Is it like a trip to help me get over my heartache?
Y'know, it is a good thing I asked Maruo to get me a ticket!
I felt like takin' a trip to Tokyo too, so I am taggin' along!
I only went on this trip so I could be alone and think things over quietly...
Man, travel an' frozen tangerines go together like bread an' butter!
I do have one more tangerine...
They taste better before they thaw.
By the way, how can you afford this?
Oh, I had money saved up from my part-time job.
And then I sold some old records.
You do not have nearly enough...
Well, if I can make it to Brother Jun's place, I am sure it will work out.
Ri'ko said the food in the dining car is probably expensive,
so she made these for us.
Are not you going to eat it?
She is been worried about you.
W-What is with all these people?!
Tokyo Station is always like this.
Why do not you go sightseeing around Tokyo?
I want to see what your mom's like, so I am comin' with you.
W-Wait, maybe I got the address wrong...
Well, let us go in an' ask.
I have changed my mind about meeting her...
It is better if I do not see her...
Even if I did, I am sure...
She says it is your mom's day off today.
Said she would meet you here tomorrow afternoon.
So we will come back then.
Alright, I say we relax a bit at Brother Jun's place!
Do you two have business with Katsuragi Junichi-kun?
Well, there is no point in waiting for him.
He is been missing since last month.
Rumor has it he got in bad with some faction and now he is in hiding.
Although it is possible he is just shacking up with some girl...
That guy's popular with college girls...
Yeah, that does not surprise me...
Have you two come all the way from Kyushu?
You would not believe how stupid this guy is!
He is no end of trouble!
When I am with him, his stupidity rubs off on me!
You are lucky to have such a good buddy.
Sounds like it is the most!
Pretty rare to have a friend you can get goofy with.
Unlike love affairs, friendship is for life.
Kaoru, that is you, is not it?
What are you standing around like a scarecrow for?!
I have never eaten fancy curry like this before!
Go on, do not be shy.
I like the way you shovel it in.
I have got a thing for men with a hearty appetite.
She is not at all like I imagined her to be.
Mother and son perfectly in unison!
Or more like, we play music together.
He is a drummer and I play the piano...
Oh, Kaoru, you used to love it when your dad played the piano.
He would play and I would sing along...
And then, even if you were crying, you would always stop and listen...
That is such a happy memory...
I do not remember at all...
And anyway, Dad never likes to talk about the past...
Who would want to talk about a washout of a mother like me?
Looks like the rain has stopped,
so I am going to take a little stroll around Ginza.
I think he wanted to give us some time alone.
But eat before it gets cold.
By the way, how is school?
Is there a girl that you like?
I would rather not talk about that right now...
Well, just the idea of the baby boy in my memory
who would say Mama and make gurgling noises... having a broken heart!
You are in the heyday of youth!
Not bad, not bad at all!
the more whatever had been building up inside me disappeared into thin air.
I thought you were not going to make it in time.
The song called Lullaby of Birdland.
Listen and then try singing along to it.
I will come back to visit you again...
But this is in English, is not it?
I do not know the language at all...
Jazz is best when sung by a woman with a husky voice.
I will come back for sure, so practice, Mom, practice!
Thank you for coming to see me...
I would probably never see you again...
That is what I told myself...
Why did my mom leave me behind?
Those words that I could not ask flew away somewhere with this scenery...
Mom's mouth formed the words, I am sorry.
I shook my head, but I am not sure she saw it.
